cs.DS, cs.BIO, cs.IR, cs.CE, cs.DB 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the design and construction of data structures for efficient indexing of large genomic databases. 
- cs.BIO (Bioinformatics) is also likely as the paper specifically mentions indexing partial and whole human genomes for read alignment. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possibility as the paper discusses methods for accessing and searching large genomic databases. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possibility as the paper discusses the practical application of the indexing method for read alignment. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is a possibility as the paper discusses the construction of an index for large genomic databases.
